The paper deals with optimization problems in machine learning, specifically non-convex matrix factorization, and applies the framework to matrix completion and robust PCA. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses sample complexity and information-theoretic lower bounds, which are related to Information Theory (cs.IT). The use of optimization techniques and algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the framework to specific problems, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
